    <h2 class="font-bold text-center text-xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-violet-400 mt-32 mb-8">Deafblindness</h2>

    <p class="text-lg/loose md:text-xl/loose lg:text-2xl/loose max-w-prose mb-8">Deafblindness is a sensory disability that combines both deafness and blindness. Most people who are Deaf-Blind retain some hearing and sight capabilities. </p>

    <p class="text-lg/loose md:text-xl/loose lg:text-2xl/loose max-w-prose mb-8">One of the only options for someone who is Deaf-Blind is a refreshable braille display. These devices have screen readers that instead of speaking the text aloud, send the line of text to a braille display. Users read the line of text then press a button to go to the next line. Braille displays can be attached to regular computers as a supplement to a main keyboard. Users often switch between the keyboard for typing and braille display for reading. </p>

